{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "66bcbfd6ae81d148616b2485", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "MOG", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9b"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "615d92f0de3d91842a5cf858", "title": "NEET 2019 (Odisha)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "Two identical capacitors $C_1$ and $C_2$ of equal capacitance are connected as shown in the circuit. Terminals a and $\\mathrm{b}$ of the key $\\mathrm{k}$ are connected to charge capacitor $\\mathrm{C}_1$ using battery of emf $\\mathrm{V}$ volt. Now, disconnecting a and $b$ the terminals $b$ and $c$ are connected. Due to this, what will be the percentage loss of energy?\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/neet/52YMb6ndY_vosk9jDV-qVrbP1uhUel1QRWre4Ok1s8I.original.fullsize.png\">", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "HEc6L", "text": "$75 \\%$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "4QaH8", "text": "$0 \\%$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "PUcLh", "text": "$50 \\%$", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "dgWkU", "text": "$25 \\%$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "When $\\mathrm{C}_1$ is connected to voltage source, it is charged to a potential $V$ and this will be stored as a potential energy in the capacitor given by\n$$\n\\mathrm{U}=\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{CV}^2\n$$\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/neet/Gs3-r0DS_3RFo5hBxn9OBehSms5SzyNuPRc8yWf6I54.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\nWhen key is disconnected from battery and band c are connected, the charge will be transformed from the capacitor $\\mathrm{C}_1$ to capacitor $\\mathrm{C}_2$, then<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/neet/wDkUS_T4XjHPNz7SlEsLbSzpV8VfnuH5sXyWvl1WEWU.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\nThe loss of energy due to redistribution of charge is given by\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\begin{aligned}\n\\Delta \\mathrm{U} & =\\frac{\\mathrm{C}_1 \\mathrm{C}_2}{2\\left(\\mathrm{C}_1+\\mathrm{C}_2\\right)}\\left(\\mathrm{V}_1-\\mathrm{V}_2\\right)^2 \\\\\n& =\\frac{\\mathrm{C} \\times \\mathrm{C}}{2(\\mathrm{C}+\\mathrm{C})}(\\mathrm{V}-0)^2=\\frac{1}{4} \\mathrm{CV}^2 \\quad\\left[\\because \\mathrm{C}_1=\\mathrm{C}_2\\right]\n\\end{aligned} \\\\\n& \\therefore \\text { Percentage loss }=\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{U}}{\\mathrm{U}} \\times 100=\\frac{\\frac{1}{4} \\mathrm{CV}^2}{\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{CV}^2} \\times 100=50 \\%\n\\end{aligned}\n$$", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "137a25577cc641088dd8a66748e0ed47", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/lVe55ZL4tkEUm.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/lVe55ZL4tkEUm.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ecb", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "6788cc0b2dbc1ecacabb7026", "isFree": false}], "description": "NEET"}, "masterId": "MOGNEPYQ75926372", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "updatedAt": "2024-09-02T07:37:19.258Z", "updated_by": "65d0c176a8f74604505ba6f6", "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94